com.mansoor.uncommon.configuration.Convertors.encryption
Class KeyConfig

java.lang.Object
  com.mansoor.uncommon.configuration.Convertors.encryption.KeyConfig

public class KeyConfig
extends Object

Configuration object encapsulating information required to load a KeyStore and a Key within that Store. Client can either provide either a fully populated KeyStore or KeyStorePath, KeyStoreType and KeyStorePassword to load key store from the file systme.

To load a KeyStore from a file system, a KeyConfig will be populated as 

         new KeyConfig.Builder()
          .keyAlias("keyAlias")
          .keyPassword("keyPassword".toCharArray())
          .keyStorePassword("storePassword".toCharArray())
          .keyStoreType(EncryptionUtil.JCEKS)
          .keyStorePath("/path/to/store)
          .createKeyConfig();

To use an initialized KeyStore, configure the KeyConfig as 

         new KeyConfig.Builder()
            .keyStore(keyStore)
            .keyAlias("uncommon-key")
            .keyPassword("password".toCharArray())
            .createKeyCofig();
